    "## Normal PDF\n",
    "\n",
    "The PDF for a normal distribution is given by,\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ f(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sigma \\sqrt{2 \\pi}} \\exp\\left(-\\frac{1}{2} \\left(\\frac{x-\\mu}{\\sigma}\\right)^2  \\right) $$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.small}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "b763d85b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def norm_pdf(x, μ, σ):\n",
    "  return (1/(σ * np.sqrt(2*np.pi))) * np.exp(-0.5 * ((x - μ)/σ)**2)"
   ]
